'''多斯拉其語'''（{{lang|en|Dothraki language}}、'''多斯拉克語'''）為[[喬治·R·R·馬丁|喬治·R·R·馬丁]]的奇幻小說系列[[冰與火之歌|冰與火之歌]]及其改編的電影影集[[权力的游戏_(电视剧)|權力的遊戲]]裡所使用的[[人工語言|人工]]的[[虛構語言|虛構語言]]，在小說裡多斯拉其語是由[[冰與火之歌的世界|多斯拉其海]](World of A Song of Ice and Fire/多斯拉克海)的[[原住民|原住民]]所使用的。多斯拉其語是由語言學家[[大衛·J·彼得森|大衛·J·彼得森]]<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Do+you+speak+Dothraki%3F-a0279261433 |title=Do you speak Dothraki? |date=January 30, 2012 |work=The New York Times Upfront |accessdate=2014-04-06 |archive-date=2020-07-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200718204001/https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Do+you+speak+Dothraki%3F-a0279261433 |dead-url=no }}</ref>以馬丁小說上的多斯拉其語單詞和短語為基礎，而為電視系列影集"權力的遊戲"所開發的人工語言。 

截至2011年九月，多斯拉其語包括3,163個字詞，<ref name="wired">{{cite web |url= http://www.dothraki.com/2011/09/the-header-script/ |title= The Header Script |date= 21 September 2011. Retrieved 2011-10-03 |accessdate= 2014-04-06 |archive-date= 2019-04-17 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190417083442/http://www.dothraki.com/2011/09/the-header-script/ |dead-url= no }}</ref> 所有這些字詞還沒有被公開過。於2012年，美國有146名新生女嬰被命名為"卡莉熙"(Khaleesi)。在"多斯拉其語"(Dothraki/多斯拉克語)上這個語詞"卡莉熙"表示"卡奧"<khal>或統治者的妻子，並由"丹妮莉絲·坦格利安"(Daenerys Targaryen)在影集系列裡採用為頭銜。<ref>{{cite news|last=Wattenberg|first=Laura|title=The Ultimate 'Game of Thrones' Baby Name|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/laura-wattenberg/the-ultimate-game-of-thrones-baby-name_b_3312750.html|accessdate=22 May 2013|newspaper=[[Huffington_Post|Huffington Post]]|date=22 May 2013|archive-date=2018-06-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180618200404/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/laura-wattenberg/the-ultimate-game-of-thrones-baby-name_b_3312750.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==語言發展==
多斯拉其語的詞彙是由彼得森事前做好改編再行創建出。<!--HBO hired the [[Language_Creation_Society|Language Creation Society]] to create the language, and after an application process involving over thirty [[List_of_language_inventors|conlangers]], David Peterson was chosen to develop the Dothraki language. He delivered over 1700 words to HBO before the initial shooting. Peterson drew inspiration from George R. R. Martin’s description of the language, as well as from such languages as [[Turkish_language|Turkish]], [[Russian_language|Russian]], [[Estonian_language|Estonian]], [[Inuktitut|Inuktitut]] and [[Swahili_language|Swahili]].<ref name=hbo>{{cite web |url=http://dothraki.conlang.org/official-hbo-press-release/ |title=Official HBO Press Release |date=April 12, 2010}}</ref>

David J. Peterson and his development of the Dothraki language were featured on an April 8, 2012 episode of [[CNN|CNN]]'s ''[[The_Next_List|The Next List]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://whatsnext.blogs.cnn.com/2012/04/06/language-creation-for-game-of-thrones/|title='Game of Thrones' linguist: How to create a language from scratch |publisher=CNN What's Next}}</ref> He went on to create the [[Valyrian_languages|Valyrian languages]] for season 3 of ''Game of Thrones''.

===語言限制===
The Dothraki language was developed under two significant constraints.  First, the language had to match the uses already put down in the books. Secondly, it had to be easily pronounceable or learnable by the actors. These two constraints influenced the grammar and phonology of the language: for instance, voiceless stops can be aspirated or unaspirated, as in English.-->

